cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.SI, cs.MM. 

Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): Compressed sensing is a topic closely related to information theory, and this paper proposes a new architecture for compressed sensing reconstruction. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The use of sparsifying basis and permutation in compressed sensing can be seen as a form of machine learning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition): Compressed sensing has been widely used in image and video compression, and the proposed architecture may have applications in this field. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks): Compressed sensing has also been applied in network sensing and monitoring, and the parallel reconstruction architecture may have implications in this area. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia): Similar to cs.CV, compressed sensing has been used in multimedia applications such as audio and speech compression, and the proposed architecture may have relevance in this field.
